  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  sourcePage 20
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line 20
  line `( d ) inspected at least once in a week for identifying any leakage and deterioration thereof and`
  line `shall be documented.`
  line `CHAPTER VIII`
  line `P REVENTION OF MARINE POLLUTION AND LIABILITY FOR ENVIRONMENTAL EMERGENCY`
  line `38. Committee to ensure compliance of international obligations. — ( 1 ) The Committee shall`
  line `ensure compliance of any activity undertaken in the Antarctic environment and dependent and`
  line `associated ecosystems by the permit holder, including compliance of such International Conventions`
  line `or Treaty or Protocol or such other international obligations, as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 2 ) The permit holder shall maintain records of all waste and sewages, including all introductions`
  line `and discharges into the marine environment caused by operation of vessels as part of the activity and`
  line `the said records shall be submitted to the Director General appointed under the Merchant Shipping`
  line `Act, 1958 (44 of 1958) and the Committee, whenever required.`
  line `39. Duties and liabilities of Operator in case of environmental emergency. — ( 1 ) If an`
  line `environmental emergency occurs from any activity in Antarctica and dependent and associated`
  line `ecosystems, the Operator shall, without delay, take effective response action and inform the`
  line `Committee and the Director General appointed under the Merchant Shipping Act, 1958 (44 of 1958)`
  line `of such environmental emergency and thereafter, the Committee shall transmit it to the Parties to the`
  line Treaty.
  line `( 2 ) If no response action is taken by the Operator under sub - section ( 1 ) and the nature of the`
  line `environmental emergency requires immediate response action, the Party, where the vessel or aircraft is`
  line `registered, may undertake such action on behalf of the Operator, and the Operator shall be liable to pay`
  line `the cost of such response action taken by the Party or Parties, as may be prescribed in accordance with`
  line `Annex VI to the Protocol.`
  line `( 3 ) If no response action is taken by the Operator or by any Party or Parties, the Operator shall be`
  line `liable to such penalty as may be prescribed in accordance with Annex VI to the Protocol.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, the expression “ environmental emergency ” means`
  line `any unforeseen or accidental event that results in, or imminently threatens to result in, significant and`
  line `harmful impact on the Antarctic environment.`
  line `40. Exemption of Operator from liability in certain cases. — An Operator shall not be liable for`
  line `an environmental emergency under section 39, if it is proved that such emergency is caused by —`
  line `( a ) an act or omission that was necessary to protect human life;`
  line `( b ) a natural disaster of an extraordinary nature which could not reasonably be foreseen and`
  line `the Operator had taken all reasonable measures to reduce the risk and potentially harmful effects`
  line `of the environmental emergency;`
  line `( c ) an act of terrorism; and`
  line `( d ) an act of war aimed at the Operator's activity:`
  line `Provided that the Operator shall submit an explanation to the Committee of his act or omission`
  line `within a period of sixty days from the date of such emergency, stating the reasons therefor.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-21
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Page 21`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  sourcePage 21
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line 21
  line `CHAPTER IX`
  line `O FFENCES AND PENALTIES`
  line `41. Penalty for contravention of certain provisions of Act by person. — Any person who`
  line `contravenes the provisions of, —`
  line `( a ) section 4 or section 5 or section 8 or section 12 or section 18 or section 19 or section 20 or`
  line `section 21 or sub - section ( 4 ) of section 29 or section 36 or section 37, shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine which shall not be less than`
  line `ten lakh rupees but which may extend to fifty lakh rupees, or with both;`
  line `( b ) section 7 or section 9 or section 10, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to seven years and with fine which shall not be less than ten lakh rupees but`
  line `which may extend to fifty lakh rupees;`
  line `( c ) section 17, shall be punishable, with —`
  line `( i ) an imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than twenty years but which may`
  line `extend to imprisonment for life and with fine which shall not be less than fifty crore rupees for`
  line `any nuclear explosion in Antarctica; and`
  line `( ii ) an imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than fourteen years but which may`
  line `extend to imprisonment for life and with fine which shall not be less than twenty - five crore`
  line `rupees for disposal of any radioactive waste material in Antarctica.`
  line `( d ) section 11 or section 16 or section 33 or section 35, shall be punishable with imprisonment`
  line `for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine which shall not be less than fifteen lakh`
  line `rupees but which may extend to seventy - five lakh rupees, or with both;`
  line `( e ) section 14 or section 32, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to one year, or with fine which shall not be less than five lakh rupees but which may extend`
  line `to twenty lakh rupees, or with both.`
  line `42. Penalty for contravention of certain provisions of Act involving vessel. — Where the`
  line `contravention involves a vessel under this Act, the Operator of such vessel shall be punishable, —`
  line `( a ) for contravention of section 6 or section 11 or section 12 or section 13 or section 18 or`
  line `section 19 or section 21 or section 22, with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three`
  line `years, or with fine which shall not be less than one crore rupees but which may extend to five`
  line `crore rupees, or with both;`
  line `( b ) for contravention of section 7 or section 9 or section 39, with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to seven years and with fine which shall not be less than two crore rupees but`
  line `which may extend to ten crore 1 rupees.`
  line `43. Penalty for contravention of certain provisions of Act involving aircraft. — Where the`
  line `contravention involves an aircraft under this Act, the Operator of such aircraft shall be punishable, —`
  line `( a ) for contravention of section 6 or section 11 or section 12 or section 19 or section 21, with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine which shall not be less than`
  line `one crore rupees but which may extend to five crore rupees, or with both;`
  line `* By corrigendum.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-22
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Page 22`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  sourcePage 22
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line 22
  line `( b ) for contravention of section 9, with imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven`
  line `years and with fine which shall not be less than two crore rupees but which may extend to ten`
  line `crore 1 rupees.`
  line `44. Penalty where no provision made in Act. — Any person who contravenes the provisions of`
  line `this Act or fails to comply with any provision thereof which it was his duty to comply with, and in`
  line `respect of which no penalty is specifically provided in this Act, shall be punishable with fine which`
  line `may extend to ten lakh rupees.`
  line `45. Offences by companies. — ( 1 ) Where any offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who at the time the offence was committed was in - charge of, or was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company as well as the company,`
  line `shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub - section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had`
  line `exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub - section ( 1 ), where any offence under this Act has`
  line `been committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent`
  line `or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or`
  line `other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “ company ” means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line `( b ) “ director ”, in relation to a firm, means a partner of the firm.`
  line `CHAPTER X`
  line `M ISCELLANEOUS`
  line `46. Constitution of fund. — ( 1 ) There shall be constituted a fund to be called the Antarctic Fund`
  line `and there shall be credited thereto, —`
  line `( a ) all fees received for grant of permit and charges collected for Antarctic related activities`
  line `under this Act;`
  line `( b ) any grant or loans that may be made by the Central Government for the purposes of this`
  line `Act; and`
  line `( c ) any grant or loans that may be made by any institution for the purposes of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) The fund shall be applied towards the welfare of Antarctic research work and protection of`
  line `Antarctic environment.`
  line `( 3 ) The Committee shall maintain and administer the fund in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line `47. Security for permit by certain persons. — ( 1 ) The Committee may require such applicants to`
  line `deposit such amount as security in such form as may be prescribed.`
  line `* By corrigendum.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-23
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Page 23`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  sourcePage 23
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line 23
  line `( 2 ) The security amount may be applied by the Committee to reimburse the Government, either`
  line `fully or partially, for reasonable costs incurred by the Government in preventing, mitigating or`
  line `remedying any adverse environmental impact caused by the permit holder or persons or vessels bound`
  line `by conditions of the permit.`
  line `48. Designated Court and jurisdiction. — ( 1 ) For the purposes of providing speedy trial of`
  line `offences under this Act, the Central Government, after consulting the Chief Justice of the concerned`
  line `High Court or High Courts as it may consider necessary, shall specify by notification, one or more`
  line `Court of Sessions, to be the Designated Court and may specify the territorial jurisdiction of such`
  line Court.
  line `( 2 ) The Designated Court shall have jurisdiction to try any offence punishable under this Act.`
  line `( 3 ) No Designated Court shall take cognizance of an offence punishable under this Act except`
  line `upon a complaint in writing made by an officer authorised in this behalf by the Central Government by`
  line notification.
  line `( 4 ) The Designated Court may, upon perusal of a complaint made under this Act, take cognizance`
  line `of that offence without the accused being committed to it for trial.`
  line `( 5 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), for`
  line `the purposes of conferring jurisdiction, an offence under this Act, committed by any person or`
  line `Operator in Antarctica shall be deemed to have been committed in India.`
  line `( 6 ) While trying an offence under this Act, the Designated Court may also try an offence under`
  line `any other law, other than an offence under this Act with which the accused may be charged at the`
  line `same trial under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line `49. Report to Committee of offences. — Where an offence under this Act has been committed, the`
  line `officer designated by the Committee or the head of a station in Antarctica or an Operator shall`
  line `immediately report to the Committee of such offence and thereafter, the Committee shall transmit it to`
  line `the Central Government for necessary action.`
  line `50. Conferment of powers of investigation, etc. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), for the purposes of this Act, the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification, confer on any officer of the Central Government or State Government or`
  line `Committee, the power of arrest, investigation, search and seizure and prosecution exercisable by a`
  line `police officer under the said Code.`
  line `( 2 ) The officers of police shall assist the officer referred to in sub - section ( 1 ), in the execution of`
  line `the provisions of this Act.`
  line `51. Application of Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 to proceedings before Designated`
  line `Court. — Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure,`
  line `1973 (2 of 1974) shall apply to the proceedings before a Designated Court and the person conducting a`
  line `prosecution before a Designated Court shall be deemed to be a Public Prosecutor.`
  line `52. Accounts and audit of fund. — ( 1 ) The Committee shall maintain proper accounts and other`
  line `relevant records in relation to the fund and prepare an annual statement of accounts, including the`
  line `profit and loss account and the balance - sheet, in such form as may be prescribed, in consultation with`
  line `the Comptroller and Auditor - General of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-24
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Page 24`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  sourcePage 24
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line 24
  line `( 2 ) The accounts of the fund shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor - General of India at`
  line `such intervals as may be specified by him.`
  line `53. Returns and reports. — ( 1 ) The Committee shall furnish to the Central Government, at such`
  line `time and in such form and manner as may be prescribed, or as the Central Government may direct,`
  line `such returns and statements with such particulars with regard to any proposed or existing programme`
  line `for the promotion and development of the environmental protection in Antarctica, as the Central`
  line `Government may, from time to time, require.`
  line `( 2 ) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub - section ( 1 ), the Committee shall, as soon as possible`
  line `after the end of each financial year, submit to the Central Government a report in such form and`
  line `manner as may be prescribed, giving a true and full account of its activities, policies and programmes`
  line `undertaken during the previous financial year.`
  line `54. Protection of action taken in good faith. — No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against the Central Government, State Government or the Committee or its members, officers`
  line `and other employees or any officer authorised by the Central Government or the Committee for`
  line `anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of the provisions of this Act.`
  line `55. Power to make rules. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may make rules to carry out the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for all or`
  line `any of the following matters, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the Antarctic Specially Protected Area and Marine Protected Area under section 11;`
  line `( b ) any other species under clause ( d ) of sub - section ( 1 ) of section 14;`
  line `( c ) substance or product which shall not be introduced into Antarctica under section 19;`
  line `( d ) historic site or monument or its part under section 20;`
  line `( e ) the allowances or fees for nominated members under sub - section ( 4 ) and the procedure to`
  line `be followed by members under sub - section ( 5 ) of section 23;`
  line `( f ) the intervals at which the Committee shall meet, the rules of procedure in regard to`
  line `transaction of business at its meetings and its quorum under section 24;`
  line `( g ) the form of application for permit, particulars and fees under sub - section ( 2 ) of section 27;`
  line `( h ) the terms and conditions of the permit under sub - section ( 3 ) of section 27;`
  line `( i ) other significant detrimental effects on the Antarctic environment and its dependent and`
  line `associated ecosystems under clause ( g ) of sub - section ( 4 ) of section 27;`
  line `( j ) the manner of carrying out environmental impact assessment to be conducted by the`
  line `applicant under sub - section ( 5 ) of section 27;`
  line `( k ) the manner of preparing waste management plan and emergency plan under sub - section ( 6 )`
  line `of section 27;`
  line `( l ) the period for which permit may be granted and fee to be paid for its renewal under`
  line `sub - section ( 7 ) of section 27;`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-25
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Page 25`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  sourcePage 25
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line 25
  line `( m ) the qualification and experience of an officer to be designated as Inspector under`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) and other functions of the Inspector under clause ( g ) of sub - section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 30;`
  line `( n ) the manner of carrying out inspections under sub - section ( 1 ), the qualifications and`
  line `experience of an Analyst under sub - section ( 2 ) and other powers and functions of the inspection`
  line `team under sub - section ( 10 ), of section 31;`
  line `( o ) any other waste under clause ( f ) of sub - section ( 2 ) and other areas in respect of which an`
  line `inventory of locations may be prepared under sub - section ( 6 ), of section 34;`
  line `( p ) such other waste under clause ( n ) of sub - section ( 1 ) and the standards for effluent`
  line `discharge under the proviso to sub - section ( 3 ), of section 35;`
  line `( q ) the standards for emission of combustible waste, equipment and vehicles under`
  line `sub - section (2) of section 36;`
  line `( r ) other International Conventions or Treaty or Protocol or other international obligations`
  line `which the permit holder shall comply under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 38;`
  line `( s ) the cost of response action under sub - section ( 2 ) and the amount of penalty to be paid by`
  line `the Operator under sub - section ( 3 ), of section 39;`
  line `( t ) the manner in which the Committee shall maintain and administer the fund under`
  line `sub - section (3) of section 46;`
  line `( u ) the category of applicants who may deposit security with the Committee, the form of such`
  line `deposit and the security amount under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 47;`
  line `( v ) the form in which the Committee shall prepare an annual statement of accounts under`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) of section 52;`
  line `( w ) the time within which and the form and manner in which the Committee shall furnish to`
  line `the Central Government, the returns and statements under sub - section ( 1 ) and the form and`
  line `manner of report under sub - section ( 2 ), of section 53; and`
  line `( x ) any other matter which is to be, or may be prescribed.`
  line `56. Power to remove difficulties. — If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official Gazette, make such`
  line `provisions not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to it to be necessary for`
  line `removing the difficulty:`
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of a period of three`
  line `years from the date of commencement of this Act.`
  line `57. Rules, notifications or orders made or issued to be laid before Parliament. — 1 Every rule`
  line `made and every notification or order issued under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `made or issued, before each House of Parliament while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the`
  line `expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both`
  line `Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or notification or order or both Houses agree that`
  line `the rule or notific ation or order should not be made or issued, the rule, notification or order shall`
  line `* By corrigendum.`
